user_prompt_template:
As of {as_of}, does {company}'s drawdown look cyclical/sentiment-driven (a temporary, external, or fixable problem — a demand cycle, a regulatory overhang, a leverage problem fixable by refinancing/cost cuts, a manufacturing execution problem in an otherwise-viable business) rather than a structural business breakdown (permanent demand destruction, the core product/service becoming obsolete, an unfixable competitive position)? Score 4 (clearly cyclical/fixable), 2 (unclear/mixed), or 0 (looks structural) — based only on what was true and knowable as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, does {company}'s balance sheet/leverage look reasonable relative to its sector norm (not stretched)? Score 2 (doesn't look stretched), 1 (uncertain/no clear signal), or 0 (looks stretched) — based on P/B ratio, sector, and company description as of {as_of} only.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

P/B ratio (if known): {pb_ratio}

As of {as_of}, does {company}'s sector/theme have a genuine multi-year tailwind (not just a short-term bounce)? Score 4 (genuine multi-year tailwind), 2 (neutral), or 0 (headwind) — based on what was true and knowable as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, does {company}'s description or recent history suggest a real inflection point (new leadership, restructuring, a product cycle) rather than 'waiting for the same thing to eventually work'? Score 3 (real inflection point), 1 (unclear), or 0 (no visible catalyst) — based on what was true and knowable as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

Given the full scored rubric below for {company} (all other criteria's scores and reasoning), would this position fit this account's stated few-trades-per-quarter, high-conviction style — i.e. is this a name you could hold with real conviction without needing active day-to-day monitoring? Score 2 (fits) or 0 (doesn't fit / would need active monitoring).

Full scored rubric so far:
{full_rubric_results_json}

As of {as_of}, is {company} a top-tier/dominant leader in its specific market domain (clear #1 or #2, durable moat) or at least a solid niche leader (#3-4, real but not airtight moat) — durable enough to be worth holding through a full 10-year cycle regardless of near-term volatility? Or is it sub-scale/commoditized/easily disrupted? Score 5 (dominant leader), 2 (solid niche leader), or 0 (sub-scale/commoditized/disrupted) — based on {company}'s actual market position as of {as_of} only.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, does {company}'s capital allocation (R&D/capex trajectory, stated strategy, management commentary) suggest genuine, credible reinvestment into future growth, rather than declining reinvestment / harvesting cash from a maturing business? Score 2 (credibly reinvesting for growth), 1 (mixed/unclear), or 0 (harvesting, declining reinvestment) — based only on what was true and knowable as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, does {company} still have substantial, realistic runway to keep growing for years (low penetration of a large/growing addressable market, clear expansion vectors) or is it already dominant/saturated in a market that isn't itself growing much further? Score 2 (real multi-year runway), 1 (some runway, getting mature), or 0 (near-saturated, limited runway) — based only on what was true and knowable as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, given the insider transaction activity described below for {company}, does it reflect genuine open-market conviction buying (score 2), routine/ambiguous activity (score 1), or no real signal / this is actually insider selling (score 0)?

Insider transaction detail:
{insider_transaction_detail}

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, given the analyst rating activity described below for {company}, does the recent trend reflect a genuine, substantive positive shift in sell-side view (score 2), a mixed/unclear picture (score 1), or a genuine negative shift / no meaningful signal (score 0)?

Recent analyst rating activity:
{analyst_activity_detail}

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, given {company}'s insider/management ownership percentage below, does it suggest strong founder/management alignment with shareholders (score 2), an unclear/middling picture (score 1), or weak alignment (score 0)?

Insider/management ownership %: {insider_ownership_pct}

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, is there a credible, recently-disclosed Schedule 13D activist filing on {company} (an investor crossing the 5% ownership threshold with stated intent to engage management or push for strategic change)? Score 4 (recent credible 13D with a clear stated activist agenda), 2 (rumored/unconfirmed activist interest), or 0 (no known activist involvement) — based on what was publicly known as of {as_of} only.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, is there a recent cluster of open-market insider buying at {company} (multiple executives/directors buying with their own money, not routine option-exercise-and-hold or 10b5-1 scheduled sales)? Score 3 (a real recent cluster buy), 1 (isolated/unclear single insider purchase), or 0 (no known insider buying, or only routine/scheduled activity) — based on what was publicly known as of {as_of} only.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, has {company} recently received a meaningful positive analyst rating upgrade or price-target raise (a real sentiment shift, not routine coverage-initiation noise)? Score 3 (a clear recent upgrade/target raise from a credible desk), 1 (mixed/unclear analyst sentiment), or 0 (no positive analyst action, or recent downgrades) — based on what was publicly known as of {as_of} only.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, did {company} raise its forward guidance at its most recent earnings report (a genuine signal of management confidence, distinct from merely beating a prior estimate — see d24_epsbeat for that separate criterion)? Score 3 (clear guidance raise), 1 (maintained/unclear guidance), or 0 (guidance cut or withdrawn) — based on what was publicly known as of {as_of} only.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, has {company} recently received (or does it have a near-term pending) a material regulatory approval, patent grant, or similar binary regulatory catalyst (FDA approval, patent issuance, licensing approval) relevant to its business? Score 4 (recent approval already secured), 2 (credible near-term pending decision, genuinely binary/uncertain), or 0 (no relevant regulatory catalyst) — based on what was publicly known as of {as_of} only.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, is there a credible M&A rumor, announced strategic-alternatives review, or acquisition approach involving {company} (credible = reported by mainstream financial press with named sources or company confirmation, not anonymous social-media speculation)? Score 4 (company has confirmed a process or a deal is announced), 2 (credible press-reported rumor, unconfirmed by the company), or 0 (no known M&A activity) — based on what was publicly known as of {as_of} only.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, does {company} have an identifiable moat from at least one of Morningstar's five sources (network effect, intangible assets like patents/brand/licenses, cost advantage, switching costs, or efficient scale), and is it wide (durable >20yr on current trajectory), narrow (durable ~10yr), or effectively none? Score 4 (wide moat, clearly identifiable source), 2 (narrow moat, real but time-limited advantage), or 0 (no identifiable moat) - based only on what was true and knowable as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, do {company}'s executives and directors hold a meaningful equity stake (real skin in the game) with no pattern of unusual heavy selling, or does insider ownership/recent transaction activity suggest weak alignment with shareholders? Score 2 (meaningful ownership, aligned), 1 (unclear/mixed signal), or 0 (low ownership or concerning selling pattern) - based only on what was knowable as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

Insider ownership % (if known): {insider_ownership_pct}
Recent insider transactions (if known): {insider_transactions}

As of {as_of}, is most of {company}'s revenue recurring/contracted (subscription, multi-year contracts, high renewal rates) rather than one-time/transactional/cyclical? Score 3 (majority recurring, e.g. >60% subscription/contracted), 1 (mixed model), or 0 (mostly one-time/transactional) - based on the business model as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, does {company} have a diversified customer base, or is a large share of revenue dependent on a small number of large customers (a single customer >10% of revenue is a common risk flag)? Score 2 (diversified, no concerning concentration), 1 (unclear/moderate concentration), or 0 (high concentration, real dependency risk) - based only on what was knowable as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

Largest customer(s) as % of revenue (if known): {customer_concentration_pct}

As of {as_of}, is {company}'s addressable market both large relative to its current revenue (meaningful runway left) and still growing (not mature/saturated/shrinking)? Score 4 (large + growing TAM, real runway), 2 (large but mature, or growing but already well-penetrated), or 0 (small and/or shrinking market) - based only on what was knowable as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, could {company} plausibly raise prices meaningfully without losing significant volume or customers (real pricing power), or would a price increase likely drive customers to substitutes (commodity-like, no pricing power)? Score 3 (clear pricing power - brand, switching costs, or lack of substitutes), 1 (some pricing power but constrained by competition), or 0 (commodity-like, minimal pricing power) - based only on what was knowable as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, does {company}'s competitive position look like it's strengthening (gaining share, widening cost/technology lead, deepening switching costs), holding steady, or eroding (losing share, new entrants closing the gap, technology being disrupted)? Score 2 (widening/strengthening), 1 (stable), or 0 (eroding) - based only on what was knowable as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

Named competitors and recent competitive dynamics (if known): {competitive_context}

As of {as_of}, is {company} meaningfully exposed to interest-rate moves (via financing costs, real-estate-like duration, a high-multiple growth valuation, or debt-funded business model), or is it largely insensitive to rates (low debt, stable cash-generative business, reasonable valuation)? Score 2 (largely rate-insensitive - a plus for a low-frequency, long-hold account), 1 (moderate sensitivity), or 0 (highly rate-sensitive) - based on the business/balance sheet as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

Sector: {sector}. Debt level context (if known): {leverage_context}

As of {as_of}, given the prevailing economic conditions and where the business cycle appears to be (early/mid/late expansion, or contraction), is {company}'s sector positioned favorably (a cyclical tailwind, or a defensive sector holding up in a downturn) or unfavorably (a cyclical headwind for its stage of the cycle)? Score 2 (favorably positioned for the current cycle stage), 1 (neutral/unclear), or 0 (unfavorably positioned) - based only on economic conditions knowable as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

Sector: {sector}. Macro/economic context as of {as_of} (if known): {macro_context}

As of {as_of}, is {company}'s profitability meaningfully exposed to swings in commodity input costs (energy, metals, agricultural inputs) or foreign-exchange rates (large non-domestic revenue/cost base) that it doesn't control or fully hedge? Score 2 (minimal exposure - domestic, low commodity intensity), 1 (moderate exposure), or 0 (high, largely uncontrolled exposure) - based on the business model as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

Sector: {sector}. Geographic revenue mix (if known): {geo_revenue_mix}
